title: For Sale:  Zulu St Etienne Shotgun
location: Way South in Berthoud, Fort Collins, Colorado
postcontent:
I have here a really nice old piece of history.  These were converted muskets to a Snider action at a Belgiume armory for the overseas trade to Africa and America.  The base musket was French of the St. Etienne armory of France. These were converted in the 1870s to 1880's and sold as shotguns.  This is 12 gauge and IS a shooter for BLACK POWDER ONLY!   This has a working firing pin, Lock is tight and strong.  Trigger functions well and will chamber a brass 12 gauge shell .
This would be a hoot to shoot and would make an Indian Wars re-enactment piece .
I will ship it dis-assembled barrel from the stock ( a pin and a screw to re-assemble. )
Bore is good - stock was cut-down for a childs reach and then re-attached.
Stock is walnut - has normal nicks and dings of an old antique that has seen use and is wanting a bit more use in its' old age. 
 I am open to offers and negotiation - cash, money order or paypal combination.

title: For Sale:  1940 M38 Russian Mosin Nagant carbine
postcontent:
I picked this up the other day with the delusion i'd be able to keep it in my collection for a while, but we got the house we have been wanting so it has to go to help with the moving costs.

It's a solid shooter grade rifle. made in 1940, Non matching serial numbers. The M38 is the same rifle as the M44 and Type 53 in every respect save it never had a side folding bayonet. These were generally issued to rear echelon troops with little need for a bayonet.

This is a second year of production rifle. This one is not as much a collector (very little interest there for a mutt like this) but as a general shooter, hunter. base for a custom build, it's the place to be. Condition is fair to good. the bore is weak, but still serviceable. (If you want to replace it for an accurized target shooter or whatever, i can put you on a site that has original and custom bull barrels for sale) Someone has replaced the rear sight blade with a mojo peep style. No import stamps.

It is what it is, a solid shooter that you can go several directions with.

Pick up at my place in camdenton/linn creek

No trades
$250 Firm

title: For Sale:  Kimber Super Carry Ultra 3" 1911 .45ACP
postcontent:
Good evening.  Due to a recent policy change at work (one I'm not happy about), up for sale is my EDC Kimber Super Carry Ultra custom.  

3" barrel, chambered for .45 ACP, with ambidextrous thumb safety and several Kimber custom job mods: enhanced trigger job (lighter pull, ~3.5 lbs, zero slack), match grade barrel, scallops instead of checkering for grip on both the front/back strap and slide, and premium slide coating (Keratote if I'm not mistaken).  Dehorned all the way around for snag-free carry.  Not a sharp or semi-sharp edge on this pistol.  

Purchased Xmas 2012 (I'm the original owner), with ~350 rounds put through it.  I deploy often, so it sits in my safe for months at a stretch.  It IS my EDC, and has slight holster wear on the slide finish.  However this does not in any way affect the function of the gun.  

Comes with 2x 7-round Kimber magazines, each with extended Wilson floor plates.  I have the original floor plates, as well as extra bumpers if you want them.  

Comes with the 2x holsters shown (a RH straight up/down or FBI cant ride with spare mag holder and a Crossbreed IWB clone).  Also comes with factory original hard case, take down tools, a handful (~10) snap caps, 20x rounds of 50-grain civil defense rounds (HP, muzzle velocity ~2,000 fps, shatter and discharge energy completely upon impact, similar to the Hornady critical defense rounds), and about 300 range-quality ball rounds....I'm getting out of .45 so you get it all.  

Asking $1,100 firm.  It's worth it.  If you're on the fence or not convinced, come meet me at my range and test drive it for a few mags.  I'd do the same if I was considering spending my hard-earned money, so I have no objections if you want to do so.  

All the basics apply: must have drivers license or state/military ID and a CCW or some other ID.  Must be willing to sign a basic bill of sale for CYA purposes.  I'm in Arlington and can meet within a reasonable distance.  Weekdays after 7pm and weekends are pretty open.  REDACTED.  Email anytime, or call/text between 7am - 10pm.  Please no calls or texts after 10.  Sorry, but I don't do Paypal or Bitcoin or any other online forms of payment.  Strongly prefer F2F, but will ship to your FFL if you're willing to pay costs both ways.  

Questions ? Ask 'em.  I'm not interested in trades, this is a for sale post only.  Thanks.
